quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  4,105,Verily We! We have sent down the Book unto thee With truth that thou mightest judge between people by that which Allah hath shewn thee; and be not thou On behalf of the deceivers a pleader
  4,106,And beg thou forgiveness of verily Allah is ever Forgiving
  4,107,"And contend thou not for those who defraud their souls verily Allah loveth not one who is a defrauder, sinner"
  4,108,"They feel ashamed of men and feel not ashamed of Allah, whereas He is Present with them when by night they plan together of discourse which pleaseth Him not; and Allah is of that which they work ever an Encompasser"
  4,109,"Lo! it is ye who have contended for them in the life of the world; then who will contend for them with Allah on the Day of Resurrection, or who shall be their champion"
  4,110,"And whosoever worketh an ill or wrongeth his own soul, and thereafter beggeth forgiveness of Allah shall find Allah Forgiving, Merciful"
  4,111,"And whosoever earnoth a sin, only against his own soul he earnoth it; and Allah is ever Knowing, Wise"
  4,112,"And whosoever earnoth a vice or a sin, and thereafter casteth it on an innocent, he hath surely borne a calumny and a manifest sin"